						               													<description>Hail Caesar! is a miniatures gladiator game created by David P. Gundt and his local gaming club, Melees Gloriosus.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;quot;Hail Caesar!&amp;quot; is a simple &amp;quot;beer and pretzels&amp;quot; type gladiator game in which character have simple statistics (strength, stamina, speed, dexterity, skill) and are pitted against each other.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;What really makes the game fun is the amount of research that Mr. Gundt put into the game. Rules for ten different types  of gladiators and a great plethora of weaponry and armor are included with the game. Perhaps the most interesting are the rules included for the Andabates type gladiator, a gladiator that fought blind with a full-head helmet, sort of like Luke Skywalker in &amp;quot;Star Wars Episode IV: A New Hope.&amp;quot;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Hail Caesar! is a fun &amp;quot;beer and pretzels&amp;quot; gladiator game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
